<!-- 
Specifies which form fields will be generate in drupal 
see https://api.drupal.org/api/drupal/developer%21topics%21forms_api_reference.html/7.x for info about drupal form render api. 

In the fields section you can specify fields. Fields need to have attributes:
- id: unique id which will become the form field id in drupal
- name: name of the field in the original  cmdi-profile

and children:
- type: formatting of the field; implemented values are
    * textfield
    * date
    * dropdown 
    * (empty) missing values will be rendered as textfield

- title: The title which will appear on top of the field



- description (optional): a info button which will show the value this field when hovered onto
- subNode (optional): specifies whether a field is located in a subNode.

Additional fied is data. data fields are hidden in drupal. Required info is the clarin profile ID, to which this transform refers 
  
 -->

